                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/835</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of the American
                        Republics</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Duggan</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-20">July 20,
                            1937</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Huneeus of the Chilean Embassy telephoned to say that the Ambassador, who is
                    out of town, just received an instruction from the Foreign Office stating that
                    the Chilean representative at the Chaco Peace Conference has been instructed to
                    work in “full agreement” with the representative of the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Laurence Duggan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
